---
<section class="wedge">
  <div class="inner">
    <h2>Enforcement, not just prompts</h2>
    <div class="points">
      <div class="point">
        <h3>Drift-failing validators</h3>
        <p>Overlay-drift, contract-manifest, task-shape, and hook-guardrail checks that exit non-zero when policy drifts.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="point">
        <h3>Self-verifying generated code</h3>
        <p>Every generated validator carries a hash of its own rendered source; the harness refuses to run a check that's been hand-edited rather than silently trusting drifted policy.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="point">
        <h3>Hard safety boundaries</h3>
        <p>Symlink-resolving path safety, traversal rejection, and injection-as-data rendering, all backed by adversarial tests.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .wedge {
    background: var(--surface-alt);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding: 4rem 1.5rem;
  }

  .inner {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: clamp(1.25rem, 2.5vw, 1.625rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.015em;
    color: var(--text-strong);
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .points {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(240px, 1fr));
    gap: 2rem;
  }

  .point h3 {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text-strong);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }

  .point p {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--text-body);
    margin: 0;
  }
</style>
